Here's another guide you can follow in order to push a local repository into GitHub. Hope you enjoy!

For creating a new repository:
git config --global user.email "@gmail.com" 
git config --global user.name "jgjghj"

git config --global --unset init.defaultBranch
git config --list 
git init
git add . 
git commit -m "Commit 1"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin [the link of your repository]

git push -u origin main 
Username for 'https://github.com/':  [your username]
Password for 'https://github.com/': [your token]



For update an existing repository: 
git add . 
git commit "Commit 2"
git push -u origin main
Username for 'https://github.com/': [your username]
Password for 'https://github.com/': [your token]
